content.detailedDescription: I was taking my dog out and  i was standing at the base of the fir trees and noticed something moving really fast behind the trees about 2/3 the way up the treeline. i caught this of the out of the corner of my eye only because the object was really moving.I never even saw a jet move that fast. i thought it was a falling star so i watched it until it come out from behind the treeline. it moved the span of the whole tree, limb to limb in about 7 seconds and then came out into a clearing. the object seemed to be moving in a straight line(no zig zagging motion)it made 90 degree turn to the left and sped up out of sight. there was no noise at all. it was a few minutes to 9:oopm sept. 18th 2009
content.summary: Unusual  aircraft/anomaly

content.detailedDescription:
I experienced a local blackout at my apartments, which didn't seem to affect all apartments so i am unsure of at this time the extent of it but i am quite sure it affected at least four buildings (each one has 24 residences). as of this morning, dominion power did not list anything on it's real-time outage map. i may contact them to get more information on the outage.

during this blackout i awakened a couple times in hopes that the power had come back on. around 1am in the morning i woke up and walked around to check on things. i walked over to the bedroom window to look out the window blinds briefly and as soon as i did i spotted what looked like 4 or 5 bright lights *star-like" right next to one another or overlapping each other creating a rectangular-object effect. from my window, this object was sitting in the visible sky just above the roof of the apartment building right next to mine. it seemed like it was probably a good couple miles at the least in the distance. no more than a few seconds later this object just vanished in the spot it appeared to be hovering in as if covered by a quickly moving invisible cloud or if the lights came off quickly one after another.

to me, it was not your typical aircraft in the distance light signature and i have never seen that type of signature before. i believe it is possible it could have been an aircraft with a particular light formation that i am not used to seeing, maybe even a few f-22's flying very close together or hovering together during an unknown night exercise from the nearby langley afb. we are near newport news international airport and do have maybe a medium-level of aircraft traffic in the sky. not sure what to make of this one however. 

and afterwards, i couldn't help but feel like it knew i was watching it and disappeared so i at the very least could no longer see it.
content.summary: Bright rectangular star-like object hovering in sky during a local blackout

content.detailedDescription: I was driving from tucson to sells to drop off my girlfriend who lives in a tiny community south of sells and i was just past the community of three points and was driving towards the border patrol checkpoint that is permanently stationed there.  just above kitt peak which was to the left of me on the road my girlfriend commented that a light in the sky was a ufo that she had seen many times in the past. the light was brighter than a star, a planet, or an airplane light. we stopped and looked at it for a few minutes. she said that it typically has multiple lights, that the lights would strobe, that the object sometimes would move great distances in the sky almost instantaneously, and that she could make out that it was elliptically shaped sometimes.  what i saw confirmed some of the phenomenon that she described.  it started out as being one bright light, then became two, then three, then four, the lights were in a straight line configuration and then were in an isosceles triangular pattern.  then the lights were in a straight line again and began quickly strobing.  then the lights appeared to be rotating fairly quickly in the sky.  the object moved like a precision machine.  then i saw the back of the object.  it looked like it was leaving and the afterburners were briefly illuminating the back of the object.  the back looked like it was trapezoidal in shape with the bottom of it being wider than the top.  it had some detailing on the back that looked like a protruding metal feature on the back of it.  it had a dull grey color and looked very solid.  there were no wings on the object and it was completely silent.  it definitely was not one of the surveillance blimps that are in the sky in this area at times and are used by the border patrol.  it looked too mechanical and moved too fast to be a blimp.  it was also very large.  as big as a 747.  after i saw the back of the object it disappeared.  my girlfriend says that she sees it near her home on a frequent basis and it moves to different parts of the sky.  it really freaked me out i can tell you that.
content.summary: Saw up to 4 lights moving, strobing and then rotating and then saw a solid trapezoidal object

content.detailedDescription:
My husband and i have seen two ufo sightings in the past two days. the one which i will report here took place on september 17, at 9 pm (the other happened the following day at 9:45 pm). we have seen several ufos before, as we look in the sky nearly every night, these incidences were the first two that i've not been able to rationalize or write off as possible known military crafts, or other possible known objects(though, this doesn't mean they were).

we were driving home from wickenburg, arizona, east bound on 93. at roughly 9 pm i (the passenger) looked up at the sky and saw a large, bright orange orb directly ahead of us, somewhat low on the horizon. i responded with a shock in my voice and my husbands said, "you see that too then? i've been watching it a for awhile now." 

we both continued to watch this orb. it slowly pulsed, it would be bright orange and then it would disappear completely and reappear again. after it did this a few times, suddenly there was another bright orange orb to the left of it, lower down the horizon. they both flashed in then out, and then the original one appeared to be two, right next to each other, so now there were three. all three flashed and then appeared to be five. 

the final formation was two on top, two to the left on a downward diagonal and one parallel the bottom left on a diagonal to the right - looking much like a pyramid with two top points, one on the left side, one on the left bottom, and one on the right bottom. 

then all the orbs disappeared completely.
content.summary: Orange orbs

content.detailedDescription: Hello my name is greg henry.I was interested in finding out if anyone else reported this sighting to mufon. because it was seen from as far away as wisconsin. this sighting took place on july,4 2009 between 9pm 10pm an was seen by about 4 people who were at my home shooting off fireworks.This thing to me looked like a plane on fire,but it didn't move like airplane,and it was not falling either. what i noticed was that it moved across the sky from one place to another in like five seconds. then it continued east towards port huron.So we kind of just all joked about it. but later on the next few days or so it just stayed on my mind so i went on youtube and typed in ufo sighting over michigan on the fourth of july and we were'nt the only people that saw this thing. so i would like to know if this was investicated yet or if it now. this is not the first time that i have seen somthing strange in the sky over michigan. i have very interesting story if anyone out there want to hear about it. feel to contact me at my email address turbo39622@aol.Com
content.summary: It looked like a fireball in the sky but did not fall or streek across the sky  like a meteor.

content.detailedDescription:
Heading south on carmichael rd towards home when i noticed an odd triangular object over one of the fields which appeared to be moving westward. the object had a strobe type effect which caused the object to appear to jump or skip from spot to spot. i observed the object for several minutes and just drove home. my reason for writing was cliff's description  of his event in episode three of the series. i know we are in a direct line with dover air force base and several of the military bases in md. my guess was that it was simply some type of experimental craft that was being tested. please feel free to call if you have any questions. please be fore warned that i have a voice problem that causes some problems with volume on the phone. thanks for listening. i would have never contacted anyone if i hadn't seen the program.

jim telepchak
content.summary: Triangular object quiet with strobe

content.detailedDescription:
I was sitting with my friend, talking and relaxing behind her house. we were sitting on a small hill in the grass.  the slope we sat on had a clearing about 500 meters from where we were. the trees were fairly low so that did not hinder our view of this event.  we both saw what looked like a very bright star at first,  it then glowed 10 times brighter than it was at first and  shot strait up in the air.  it was hard to judge exact distance  but i would say the trail it left in the sky had to be at least 4 feet  (  if i was measuring right in front of me )  again it's hard to judge exactly how long it really was  but if i had to guess i would say it shot out  a least a mile.

i have been told that i saw a shooting star, but i have seen many shooting stars before and for one they usually go from side to side  they are usually small and hardly visable - at least the ones i have seen.  this object i saw went strait up  and it was very large. it's hard for me to judge size with out seeing a re-creation of the event  but it was much bigger than a star ( probably because it was a lot closer?  )  .  

the really weird thing about this was the light trail it left in the sky  and the speed of which the object shot up.   the light it left stayed visable for at least two minutes afterwards.  also the rate of which this object moved was beyond me... i have never seen anything like this before. i am just hoping that maybe someone around the same time  ( i am sorry i forget the exact date  )   saw the same thing i did.  the object never made any noise and i never felt like it could be a threat. although i would love it if someone could explain this to me. 

i would have never taken this long to come out and say something but i just saw a tv show where mufon was refered and they seem very legit, unlike some of these other groups that "investigate"
content.summary: Looked like a shooting star but was way too fast large and bright to be one.

content.detailedDescription: During this past labor day weekend, my daughter and i were exiting our car in the backyard of my father's house in roseville, michigan (a suburb of detroit). it was around 10:00 pm and there were some wispy clouds, patches of clear night sky, and what appeared to be a full/new moon and a few stars. looking up at the moon to the east, i noticed what i at first thought was a bright airplane light heading from the east to the west, in line to pass directly over my father's suburban backyard. almost immediately it became apparent to me that the plane light did not resemble the typical size or color one is used to seeing on commercial or private aircraft. the color was amber and the light seemed to be a radiant light similar to the red hot rings on an electric stove. i pointed the light out to my 13 year old daughter and asked her if she could hear the "plane." neither of us could hear the typical sounds of an airplane motor or jet engine, despite the fact that the light passed directly overhead. the light seemed to be gliding and moving at a steady speed. we could not make out any object or shape above, below or around the light. the light glided into the cloud layer and was gone from sight. we discussed it and both agreed that we had seen something odd. not any type of plane or jet that we've ever seen. we went back outside to the car about 10-15 minutes later and gliding in from the east were two more of the lights we had seen earlier. again, they passed directly overhead at a fast but steady speed. the lights were all of the same size and the two lights were gliding along at the same pace, one slightly trailing the other. no commercial or private aircraft would fly that close together. it is possible they were military aircraft as selfridge afb is located in macomb county and lies to the northeast of my father's backyard. however, these military aircraft would have had to have been silent. most jet engines are noisy or would create some sound. and there were no contrails or exhaust. my daughter got a good look at the lights the second time and described a bright round amber light in the middle surrounded by a bright amber ring of light. in between was darkness. these two lights also flew into the cloud cover and they have never been seen from my father's backyard since.
content.summary: 3 ufo "lights"

content.detailedDescription: Fishing by the zilwakee bridge near bay city michigan with friends and i looked up while sitting in a lounge chair fishing and i noticed 3 points of light equally spaced moving north to south. i leaned over and asked friend if he had seen it and jokingly said he did not i was crazy and then said yes he was seeing it also. i am telling this now because i have noticed that the 3 points of light type sighting is a common one. you could tell how far the lights were apart that it was big in size...
content.summary: 3 points of light.

content.detailedDescription: I was inside the house at about 4pm the day i witnessed the object. my uncle was outside laying on a lawn ottoman or chair when i walked outside he said to me "look up" so i did, and there it was, a shiny chrome triangle just hovering there, and i was like "what the heck is that".I asked my uncle how long he had been looking at it he said for about 10 or 15 min. so i looked back up at it and its still hovering right there at about a mile up it seemed, but it was very clear that it was not man made. then i heard my mom coming into the kitchen, i looked down to tell my mom "look at this thing" as soon as i said that my uncle said "whoop there it went"(in spanish). he said "it just took off"(west).From a hovering position to just take off, that was just strange. i was 11yrs old and i know what i had seen. to this day i think i am very lucky to have witnessed this object. i now am 35yrs old living in utah for the last three years and i have seen some things out here.My daughter and i witnessed something strange together up in the skies of utah. thats another story i will let you in on next time. thanks for this opportunity to tell my(true)story.
content.summary: Chrome triangle sitting very still.

content.detailedDescription:
Myself, my girlfriend(a lounge singer), and a bass player in a local band - who eventually went on to become a priest - watched as a softly glowing blue orb moved about through the trees just outside of seremban, malaysia. the orb seemed to be radiating it's own light from within. it was about the size of a basketball and seemed to be floating through the trees but changed direction and stalled at different times. it was extremely dark on that evening and was absolutely not reflecting moonlight. there was no electric lines where we were. the object was radiating a beautiful bluish hue and we all felt it was under intelligent control. i personally felt that it was aware we were observing it. it sat at the top of a tree around a hundred feet from us and then just blinked off.  
  i just watched your program on tv - fri. night and the witnesses were observing the exact same object we witnessed in malaysia all those years ago. i find it very interesting that i witnessed the same object years ago, so many thousands of miles away.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Softly glowing blue orb

content.detailedDescription:
I let the dog out and stood on the back step and looked up at the stars as i allways do.  i noticed that part of the sky was blacked out and at first it didn't register why. then i noticed the windows in the craft and two people or beings looking right at me. they were so close that i could see the one was wareing a baseball style cap or what appeared to be one. that guy or being waved at me and my first thought was he must realize it's too late to try and do anything else but wave.  as it passed over i was to stupified to do anything but sit there and watch. 
i thought to myself this is interesting,  "must be an air force recon ship." as i passed the event through my brain i think that the ship was a lighter than air ship and that it was manouvered by electric motors, i could here just a slight buzz of some kind.
my second thought was, "they did it, the u.S. has developed a hydrogen gel,"
 (like that of aero-gel used to capture particles from commets.)
anyway, this thing and those in it seemed to me to be human and human made.  it was just a little freaky seeing this thing at 2:45 in the morning. 
the reason i haven't said anything until now is that i didn't know any place like your website exsited.  i just happened to catch your show on the tube and thought i'd check it out.
well, that's it in a nut shell, not triing to punn that because i know how these thing must sound. however it sounds your can take it for what it's worth.
content.summary: Darkened ufo passed over, blocking out the stars

content.detailedDescription:
On december 10, 1989 in napa california, i saw a very unusual "thing" in the early morning sky.  while it was years ago, i remember the day and date vividly, december 9, 1989, the day before my sighting, i got married, so it's easy for me to remember the date.

we stayed at home after our wedding, and my husband left early december 10 to run an early morning errand, so unfortunately i was home alone.  i smoke cigarettes, so i was sitting out on the patio enjoying the morning sky, smoking a cigarette. my view was towards the west.  i saw an egg shaped haze, (about the size of an egg if you held it up to the sky with your arms extended), and the best way i can explain it is, it looked like an "out of focus" patch of blue sky, as though you were looking thru a gas haze.  this patch moved from the southwest toward the northeast.  the intersting thing was the points of light within the haze.  they were in a haphazard pattern, (a least 10 of them) but as the shape moved they remained stationary.  as the haze moved, more tiny lights would appear in the front of the haze, and the lights in the back would disappear.  it was as if you were shining a flashlight against a wall in a dark room, as you move the light across the wall, the pattern in the wall remains stationary, but as the light of the flashlight moves, whats in front lights up and whats in back of it fades out.  it didn't move fast, just slowly moved across the sky, until it was out of my range of vision.

i was very upset no one else was at home to witness what i saw.  just as it moved out of view my husband returned home. dang!  

i really didn't know what it could be, but my gut feeling was, and still is, that it was something that was cloaked.  possibly a craft that has the capacity to reflect back what is surrounding it, (and on this day, it's cloaking abililty was just kinda out of whack). i know this sounds like i've watched to many movies, but it just makes the most sense to me.  at the time i called the local radio station, hoping maybe someone else saw it and made a call, but no, i was told no one else had reported any usual sightings.

i still think about it, and wonder.  that's why i needed to record what i saw with this email.  maybe it will make sense to someone else.

sincerely,
kathy hamberis
content.summary: Egg shaped haze in bright blue sky, with points of light in a haphazard pattern.

content.detailedDescription:
1. where were you and what were you doing at the time?
location: dallas pennsylvania (10 miles outside of wilkes-barre). driving south on pa route 309, pulled over at a local gas station for a better vantage point. 

2. what made you first notice the object?
bright orange fire ball off horizon (approx 45degreese off horizon), barely moving.

3. what did you think the object was when you first noticed it?
a balloon or a piece of debris on fire, not moving in the sky.

4. describe the object and its actions and motions.
the object was circular, distinct flame like qualities tracking very slowly from north to south toward the city of wilkes-barre.

5. describe your feelings, reactions and actions, during and after sighting the object.

we (a group of 4 firefighters) did not think anything of it until we spoke to friends of ours about a month later a group of (6) firefighters at a fire department 10 miles away, who noticed the exact same object 1 month later over swoyersville. this object was tracking west to east. at the sighting over swoyersville, the firefighters scrambled for a pair of binoculars, but they were unable to focus on the object.  after speaking with them i began research into what this might have been, not once did i think of a ufo. the same type object, different people, different date & time.

6. how did you lose sight of the object?

the object was out of plain sight when it went over a mountain, continuing south toward wilkes-barre.
content.summary: Fireball tracks across sky on two different dates

content.detailedDescription: I walked out on back deck around 9:20 pm est to relieve myself while letting dog out.  was attracted to turn head to left and up by (?) to see bright star (as bright as venus) like object that was traveling west to east with no sound or blinking lights but very light tail - wife also observed as i called her out to observe.  we watched it take a straight course east and disappear near tree level.  appeared high and traveling fast.  i then looked back and there was another (tree line to 180) on same course.  this one however appeared to veer slightly but stayed on course to again fade away at tree line.  lighting was steady and star like with no other colors presented.  nothing further noticed so suspecting space station and shuttle if in area.  no pictures taken or others contacted.
content.summary: Noticed bright star at approx 9:20 est, no sound, no blink followed by another.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving south on i-5 and saw a bright white light in the sky that was stationary. i saw it from about two miles away, and thought it was a helicopter at first, but as i passed it, the position in the sky and the movement made me think otherwise. i had a good view of it and could not see anything other than the light, surrounded by the night sky; i would have expected to see a glimpse of the outline of a helicopter. it appeared to only be one hundred feet or so off the ground (about the height of a near by cell antenna), at that height i really would have expected to see a helicopter. at the best viewpoint i had, the light appeared to the rotating vertically.
content.summary: Bright white light over i-5 outside of salem

content.detailedDescription: I was in my car and had just turned north onto us 19 from curlew road, in palm harbor and as i drove north in the inside lane, i observed what i first thought was a blimp to my west, and slightly ahead of me.  i imagined it was flying over the gulf, but as i drove further north, i could see there was no roundness or ovalness to it and it was white and seemed completely rectangular. my next thought was that it was a small plane pulling a banner (we see those frequently, flying over the beaches) but i could see no lettering, nor could i see a wavelike motion a banner makes as it is pulled through the air.  as i stopped at the traffic light at tampa road, i put on my distance glasses to see it more clearly, but there was no plane or banner. the object appeared to be a flat rectangle, always ahead of me but growing smaller as it moved slowly across us 19, seemingly toward the north east.  i saw a red helicopter fly toward the west, either over it or behind  - i took the helicopter to be from the coast guard, since we see them frequently too.  as i turned left (west) onto nebraska avenue the object was disappearing into the clouds behind the trees on the horizon.  the object moved very slowly and steadily always staying parallel to the ground - i kept looking for a side to show up but it seemed to have no depth.  i could see light reflecting across it and i thought it might be made of panels.  i stopped by the bb&t bank then went to walgreen's, and all the while kept searching the sky but did not see it again.  my feeling was that it just might be a ufo.  (i am 81 and have seen several in my lifetime - i feel sure they are there.)   betsy bertolino
content.summary: Looked similar to rectangle in filer's files, #37

content.detailedDescription:
My fiance & i had just left her brother's house at around 11pm, in her father's car (mid-late 70's olds cutlass), on our way to stay the night at her brother's in-laws house. the house was on a rural peninsula of the tenn. river, in the scottsboro, al area.

approximately a few hundred yards into our trip (with no house immediately close by), the clear, cool night was interrupted by a startling event. the car lost its power, the street light went out and my battery-operated seiko lcd watch (one of the first, which i still own but never use anymore) lost its power. at the same time, maybe a second or two after this occurred and having the car safely come to a stop, an incredibly bright, white light appeared off to our right side (tree side, not the side of the water). i opened my driver's side window and heard no crickets as we heard when we left her brother's house... it was dead silent.

the light stopped over our car and we tried to peer out the windshield to try and catch a glimpse of the object. after being blinded by the light, my fiancee wanted to get out to look. i cautioned her to stay in the car as we didn't know what it was. we locked our doors and sat there, trying to see what it was. after what appeared to be only a few minutes when my fiancee's watch restarted, which seemed like an eternity, the light disappeared as quickly as it had appeared. a few seconds after it left the scene (with no swoosh or other noise that we could discern), the idiot lights on the car came back on, the radio came back on and the headlights came on. i looked at my watch and, it too, had begun to work once again, as had fiancee's dial watch. i started the car and noticed the street light came back on and i heard crickets outside again, as i still had the window open (so much for using the locks). we finished our trip to town where we spent the nights during our trip.

well, 28+ years later, we still talk about that night. every so often, on long walks at night, in many areas of where we live and even places we visit, we have the street lights go out on us, but not all of them... just one or two... which may not mean anything at all in this context, but it is weird.

we once heard from a niece who grew up in alabama that her grandparents (whom we stayed with on that trip in 1981) had similar events all the time on that stretch of road, at night, on their way home.

in conclusion, i have since read and heard many stories of a similar nature, and have seen some ufo type of explanations. however, i have no idea what it was that was present that april night in 1981. i do believe in ufos and the possibility/reality of there being people other than ourselves in the universe. and, i have heard double-talk denials of something or someone in the hangers at wpafb from (now deceased) relatives who worked there. were these people just pulling my teenage leg at the time? probably... but, what if...
content.summary: Unknown power loss & white light

content.detailedDescription:
At 6:40 am on friday september 18, 2009 i stepped out the front door to get car ready to take daughter to school. my door faces north and i looked up to see venus fade with the sun coming up in the eastern sky. i unlocked the car and then looked due north and up as if to stretch. i noticed what looked like another star appear almost straight up from my location. i watched this star for about 5 minutes and found that it was moving slowly to the south. i opened my front door and asked my wife and daughter to come see what i was seeing. we watched this object for about 5 more minutes and noticed that it hade a dark see through haze about the exterior of it. it had appeared to be at about 10,000 to 20,000 feet high.
the light then began to fade then flicker then bright flash then go out. at that exact moment another light just to the left but lower lit up then flickered and flashed then went out and the again but further to the left and higher about level with the first light another light appeared then flickered and flashed and the went out. then the dark haze faded away and looked kind of like dissipating heat waves. 
the weather was nice no clouds no wind no rain. visibility was unlimited. we felt fine although a bit bewildered at the site.
content.shape: Diamond,   Flash,   Star-like,   Triangle,   Other,   Unknown
content.summary: After sun up and venus vanished as another star like object appeared.

content.detailedDescription:
Many nights in august my wife and i noticed a strange light in the western night sky when it was dark.  the lights seemed to change from white to green and then red like it was rotating.  there was also a light in the northern skydoing the same thing.  we looked at it through binoculars and it looked very mechanical the way it rotated and the lights changed in patterned color.  we looked it up on the web and it was explained as the atmosphere making a star change color.  we questioned that explanation and noticed the lights a few more nights in a row and then they were no longer visible.  
tonight on sept 17. 2009 at 10:00 pm  i was laying o the couch watching a movie and my wife walked past the kitchen window and noticed a bright light coming from the western sky again so she stopped to look at what it was.  she told me to come and look, so we stepped out into the backyard and noticed that it was the same light as before, but as we looked at it it started to fall very quickly and move left to right and then it would rise.  the whole time this was going on it seemed to be moving farther away from us.  the previous months sighting they did not noticibly move.  we could tell the were moving because the neighbors tree line is visible and the lights would fall to just above the tree line and then rise again.  i know for a fact that it was not a star.  whatever it is seems to like the area it flies over.  i would welcome someone to come and witness this for themselves.  we are going to borrow a telescope from my wifes parents so we can see it up close.  i would take a lie detector test.  my wife is someone who does not have an active imagination, so to have her see the same thing really tells me that it is a ufo.  sorry i dont have anything that would take a good picture or video or i would have.
content.summary: White, green, red, flashing rotating lights.

content.detailedDescription: I was havin a cig looked at a plane it then made a 75 degree turn down for 3-5 seconds it was way below normal flight pattern it lit up verry bright in a disk shape disapeard for 1 second and appeared again 1-2 thousand feet above and lit up again in the same dick shape then moved from south to north faster than any comercial plane ive ever seen 20 times as fast i then saw 2 strobing lights that appeared to be jets following the same tragectory but much slower then the object disapeard and when the jets were in the area i could hear the jets wierd!!! it was definatly a ufo i watch the planes all the time and they fly f16s around all the time it was not even close to any of those
content.summary: Small light moved down quick bright disk shaped light moved up fast bright disk light moved across horizon in seconds two jets behind at much slower speed

content.summary: Semi bright white ball or disc w/trail streaks across half the sky in 5 sec.

content.detailedDescription:
Our neighbors and i observed a pulsating dim red light, at about 300 yards distant.  witnesses: roderick e gouin,  brother keith j. gouin, father robert f gouin sr. neighbor timothy ellis.  we walked 300 yards toward the craft to approx 100 yards to investigate.  i was not frightend as for all of us.  a few minutes later craft rose silently to about 10 feet off the ground.  then slowly hovered away.  after a few minutes it increased in speed and disapeard twowards the south west,  never making a sound.  the next morning i investigated the area to find the growing hay was flattented in a circular pattern of about 20 feet in diameter.  personal note:  i do experience abduction dreams at a vivid level.
as opposed to sketches i will simply report it looked like a rather round bright silver disk about the size of a full size van.
content.summary: Small disk shape 20 foot diameter

content.detailedDescription: I was walking with my dog in a street near my house in ddo. i watched the planet jupiter around 45 azimuth se when i saw three small rounded objects with similar dimension ( angular ) of jupiter, however less brighter and with orange color. i saw them during 5-10 seconds moving from w to e in a trajectory similar to a shooting star, however, there was not coma or trajectory traces. no noise happened. suddenly one of them moved around the other (could be due to perspective view ) and them they disappear probable entering in the sun shadow cone around 45 azimuth. the sky was clear in that point, despite of some clouds nearby. could be a rest of some satellite or rocket, however, the movement around the other was strange for me.
content.summary: Three star-like objects moving over montreal

content.detailedDescription:

content.detailedDescription:
I have been watching the sky since an incident april 23 where i saw a blue object flash over my back yard apt. every night from at least 7-9 pm. i have recorded in a log at least 1-9 objects everyday since then, most are high up and only an amber light is seen crossing overhead and over mcarren airport and some like this one worth reporting as it defies the norms. 
first note that all the amber lights i have seen are just that, one light, no flashing or other colors ever in all my logging days. at 7:30pm i saw a dim amber white ball heading sw very high up, like a star. at 7:33pm i saw what looked like a shooting star going nw, but it looked like it was only approx. 100' up from me. . i made a note . at 8:07pm another ball appeared over my head heading e then instantly headed se with a ziggy motion for a few sec. then it dissapeared. i started to look elsewhere then a plane appeared there where there was none heading sw. made another note. then at 8:12 a bright semi-white ball shot a looong 5 sec.(1-1 thousand 2 ect) from my tree tops w (35' high) to the ne and 1/2 way across the sky over my apt. it was not as fast as a shooting star. it laft a trail behind it , like vapor with a few sparks. i couldn`t see the trail after it was gone.No sound.  alas no picture, i tried but my phone camera is not fast enough. will invest in a good night film in an unopenable package for the future. 
if you would be interested in my log book i can send a copy. it starts on april 23- aug 12 sporatic siteings and from aug. 20 to date everyday from 7-9pm everyday, sometimes longer and as some mornings i can`t sleep so sit outside.
content.summary: Semi bright white ball or disc w/trail streaks across half the sky in 5 sec.

content.detailedDescription:
I was going back inside my work from out back parking lot when i happened to notice what i at first thought was an odd looking black plane heading towards the airport. it was traveling in the manner/speed you would expect a plane to descending towards an airport until i was about to look away. it then increased speed, stopped & dropped down several hundred feet at a 90 degree angle, stopped for a moment again, sped up a bit & finally returned to a normal looking plane's flight pattern. a bus obscured my viewing it further & it was gone once the bus had passed.

since seeing the object, i've been very calm. i was having a stressful day at work & that went away after i saw it. also, i'm very forgetful about seeing it. it's one of the weirdest things i've seen i my life & it's hardly occurring to me to tell my friends and family about.
content.summary: Black object heading towards bellingham iternational airport.
